mods:mods.mods:note: Manuscript on vellum with red, black and blue Gothic letters; six large decorated initials.
Illumination: 7-line initial on f. 2 in blue with white foliate infill and red and green penwork; one-line initials throughout in red and blue.

Text: ff. [1-10]: Canon of the Mass, [begins imperfectly] ...spiritu humilitas et...; f. [10v]: blank; ff. 1-130: Missal (temporale); ff. 130v-133: slightly later additions; f. 133v: originally blank, signature of Augustinian Canon Mattheus Manscheus, dated 1526.
Binding: contemporary brown calf over boards (rebacked), with blind tooling, brass corners and center bosses, clasp broken; ms marginal notes on pastedowns.
